# UECA React Application - AI Coding Agent Instructions

## Architecture Overview

This is a **UECA (Unified Encapsulated Component Architecture)** React application - a framework that abstracts React patterns into a component model with structured props, children, methods, events, and message bus communication. UECA replaces standard React patterns with a unified component structure that emphasizes declarative composition and message-based communication.

### Learning Resources

**For New Developers**:
1. Start with UECA documentation: `node_modules/ueca-react/docs/index.md`
2. Study component patterns in `src/components/base/` for base architectures
3. Check out the full example project at: `https://github.com/nekutuzov/ueca-react-app`

**Key Documentation Files** (in node_modules/ueca-react/docs/):
- **Introduction**: `Introduction to UECA-React.md` - Framework overview and philosophy
- **Component Model**: `Component Mental Model in UECA-React.md` - Black box component architecture
- **Integration**: `Component Integration Model in UECA-React.md` - Parent-child communication patterns
- **Lifecycle**: `Lifecycle Hooks in UECA-React.md` - Component initialization and cleanup
- **State**: `State Management in UECA-React.md` - MobX-powered reactive properties
- **Bindings**: `Property Bindings in UECA-React.md` - Unidirectional, bidirectional, custom bindings
- **Events**: `Automatic onChange Events in UECA-React.md` - Auto-generated property events
- **Message Bus**: `Message Bus in UECA-React.md` - Decoupled component communication

### Component Mental Model

Components in UECA are **self-contained black boxes** with:
- **Internal State** (props): Encapsulated properties accessible and modifiable
- **Methods**: Functions to alter state, retrieve data, trigger events
- **Internal Events**: Automatic `onChange<Prop>` and `onChanging<Prop>` events
- **Children**: Recursive component structure (children follow same principles)
- **Message Bus**: Decoupled inter-component communication
- **View**: JSX presentation (if visual component)

### Technology Stack

- **UECA-React 2.0**: Framework installed as npm package `ueca-react`
  - Documentation: `node_modules/ueca-react/docs/` (comprehensive guides on all patterns)
- **TypeScript**: Core language for type safety and maintainability
- **JSX**: UI description integrated with TypeScript
- **React 19.0**: Minimal usage - only custom hooks for model instantiation
- **MobX**: Powers reactive state management (abstracted by UECA)
- **MSW**: API mocking in development
- **Plain HTML/CSS**: No UI library dependencies - all components use vanilla HTML, CSS, and SVG

**Banned React Features**: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useContext`, `useReducer`, class components
**No Material-UI**: All components are implemented with plain HTML/CSS for zero dependencies

### Key Architectural Patterns

**Component Model Structure**: All components follow the UECA pattern using `useXXX` hooks:
```tsx
type ComponentStruct = UECA.ComponentStruct<{
    props: { /* state properties */ },
    children: { /* child components */ },
    methods: { /* component methods */ },
    events: { /* event handlers */ }
}, AppMessage>;

function useComponent(params?: ComponentParams): ComponentModel {
    const struct: ComponentStruct = {
        props: { id: useComponent.name },
        View: () => <div id={model.htmlId()}>{/* JSX */}</div>
    };
    const model = UECA.useComponent(struct, params);
    return model;
}
```

**Message Bus Communication**: Components communicate via typed message bus instead of prop drilling:
```tsx
// Message definitions in src/core/infrastructure/appMessage.ts
type AppMessage = {
    "Api.GetUsers": { out: User[] };
    "Dialog.Warning": { in: { title?: string, message: string } };
};

// Posting messages
await model.bus.unicast("Api.GetUsers");  // First subscriber handles
await model.bus.broadcast("*.Input", "UI.Validate");  // All matching subscribers
await model.bus.castTo("app.form.button", "Click");  // Specific component by fullId

// Handling messages in component struct
messages: {
    "Api.GetUsers": async () => {
        return await apiClient.get<User[]>("/users");
    }
}
```

**Path Aliases** (critical for imports):
- `@components` → `src/components`
- `@core` → `src/core`
- `@api` → `src/api`
- `@screens` → `src/screens`

Configured in `tsconfig.app.json` paths and resolved by `vite-tsconfig-paths` plugin.

**TypeScript Config**:
- `strictNullChecks: false` - UECA handles undefined gracefully
- `noImplicitAny: false` - Flexibility for dynamic patterns

**Base Component Hierarchy**: All components extend from base classes in `src/components/base/`:
- `BaseModel` - Core UECA functionality with routing/dialog shortcuts
- `UIBaseModel` - UI-focused components
- `EditBaseModel` - Form/editing components with validation

**Application Architecture** (critical understanding):
```
Application (top-level orchestrator)
  ├─ AppBrowsingHistory (browser history management)
  ├─ AppSecurity (authentication & authorization)
  └─ AppUI (UI infrastructure layer)
      ├─ ErrorFallback (React error boundaries - double wrapped)
      ├─ AppBusyDisplay (global spinner/loading indicator)
      ├─ AppDialogManager (dialog system manager)
      ├─ AppAlertManager (toast notification system manager)
      ├─ FileSelector (hidden file input for file selection)
      └─ Conditional View (based on authorizedMode):
          ├─ AppLoginForm (when not authorized)
          └─ AppRouter (when authorized)
              ├─ AppLayout (main app layout with navigation)
              │   ├─ AppSideBar (collapsible sidebar)
              │   │   ├─ Toggle Button (hamburger/menu-open SVG icon)
              │   │   └─ AppMenu (navigation menu)
              │   │       └─ homeMenuItem (NavItem with SVG home icon)
              │   └─ Router → Screen Components (HomeScreen, etc.)
              └─ OtherLayout (minimal layout for standalone pages)
                  └─ Router → External/Document Views
```

**Layout Components** (`src/components/layout/layout.tsx`):
- **Block**: Basic container with padding, alignment, background color, cursor
- **Row**: Horizontal flexbox layout with spacing, dividers, alignment, cursor
- **Col**: Vertical flexbox layout with spacing, dividers, alignment, cursor
- All use plain HTML `<div>` with CSS flexbox (no Material-UI)
- Support `fill` prop to stretch in cross-axis direction
- Support `cursor` prop for interaction feedback (pointer, default, etc.)

**Component Folder Structure**: Each component is in its own folder with TypeScript and CSS files:
- `src/components/buttons/button/` - button.tsx, button.css
- `src/components/buttons/iconButton/` - iconButton.tsx, iconButton.css
- `src/components/inputs/textField/` - textField.tsx, textField.css
- `src/components/inputs/checkbox/` - checkbox.tsx, checkbox.css
- `src/components/popups/dialog/` - dialog.tsx, dialog.css
- `src/components/popups/alertDialog/` - alertDialog.tsx, alertDialog.css
- `src/components/flyouts/alert/` - alert.tsx, alert.css
- `src/components/flyouts/snackbar/` - snackbar.tsx, snackbar.css
- `src/components/flyouts/drawer/` - drawer.tsx, drawer.css
- `src/components/flyouts/alertDrawer/` - alertDrawer.tsx, alertDrawer.css
- `src/components/flyouts/alertToast/` - alertToast.tsx, alertToast.css
- `src/components/navigation/navLink/` - navLink.tsx, navLink.css
- `src/components/navigation/navItem/` - navItem.tsx, navItem.css
- `src/components/navigation/breadcrumbs/` - breadcrumbs.tsx, breadcrumbs.css
- `src/components/tabs/tab/` - tab.tsx, tab.css
- `src/components/tabs/tabsContainer/` - tabsContainer.tsx, tabsContainer.css

**Button Components** (`src/components/buttons/`):
- **Button** (`button/button.tsx`): Clickable button with variants (text, outlined, contained), sizes (small, medium, large), fullWidth support
- **IconButton** (`iconButton/iconButton.tsx`): Icon-only button with predefined icon kinds or custom icons
  - Predefined icon kinds: `ok`, `cancel`, `delete`, `refresh`, `close`
  - Can use `kind` prop for built-in icons or `iconView` prop for custom SVG
  - Sizes: small, medium, large
  - Includes `CloseIconButton` specialized factory component
- All implemented with plain HTML/CSS, no Material-UI dependencies

**Input Components** (`src/components/inputs/`):
- **TextField** (`textField/textField.tsx`): Text input field with label, placeholder, variants (outlined, filled, standard), types (text, email, password, number, tel, url, search), multiline support, error state, helper text
- **Checkbox** (`checkbox/checkbox.tsx`): Checkbox with label, sizes (small, medium, large), indeterminate state
- All implemented with plain HTML/CSS, no Material-UI dependencies

**Popup Components** (`src/components/popups/`):
- **Dialog** (`dialog/dialog.tsx`): Modal dialog with backdrop, title, content, actions
- **AlertDialog** (`alertDialog/alertDialog.tsx`): Pre-built dialog for alerts/confirmations with severity icons in title and details drawer
- All implemented with plain HTML/CSS, no Material-UI dependencies

**Flyout Components** (`src/components/flyouts/`):
- **Drawer** (`drawer/drawer.tsx`): Side panel with anchor positions (left, right, top, bottom), variants (temporary, persistent, permanent)
- **Snackbar** (`snackbar/snackbar.tsx`): Notification container with positioning, auto-hide, and close reasons (timeout, clickaway, escapeKeyDown)
- **Alert** (`alert/alert.tsx`): Alert message with SeverityIcon (success, info, warning, error), variants (standard, filled, outlined)
- **AlertDrawer** (`alertDrawer/alertDrawer.tsx`): Pre-built drawer for alert details with severity icons
- **AlertToast** (`alertToast/alertToast.tsx`): Pre-built toast notification combining Snackbar + Alert (can be used as child component for screen-specific toasts)
- All implemented with plain HTML/CSS, no Material-UI dependencies

**Navigation Components** (`src/components/navigation/`):
- **Router** (`router.tsx`): Generic routing engine with regex-based route matching, path/query params support
- **NavLink** (`navLink/navLink.tsx`): Navigation link with palette colors, underline variants (none, hover, always), disabled state, new tab support, beforeNavigate hook
- **NavItem** (`navItem/navItem.tsx`): Navigation item with three modes (icon-only, text-only, icon-text), active state, icon/text support, integrates with NavLink
  - All layout via Block/Row props (padding, cursor, alignment)
  - CSS only handles appearance (background-color, transition, color)
  - Uses CSS variables from appTheme for colors (`--nav-item-hover`, `--nav-item-disabled`, `--nav-item-active`)
  - Wraps NavLink with bidirectional bindings for transparent API
- **Breadcrumbs** (`breadcrumbs/breadcrumbs.tsx`): Navigation breadcrumb trail with semantic HTML, default arrow separator, custom separator support, fragment unwrapping, NavLink integration
- All implemented with plain HTML/CSS, no Material-UI dependencies

**Tabs Components** (`src/components/tabs/`):
- **TabsContainer** (`tabsContainer/tabsContainer.tsx`): Tab container managing multiple tabs with selection state
  - Orientation: horizontal (default) or vertical
  - Variants: standard, scrollable (with scroll buttons), fullWidth
  - Centered tabs option
  - Automatic tab selection management
  - onChange event triggered when tab selection changes
- **Tab** (`tab/tab.tsx`): Individual tab button with label, icon, disabled state, selection highlighting
  - Icon positioning: top, bottom, start, end
  - Wrapped text support for long labels
  - Invalid state styling for form validation
  - onClick event handler
  - Integration with TabsContainer for selection management
- All implemented with plain HTML/CSS, no Material-UI dependencies

**Utility Components** (`src/components/misc/`):
- **SeverityIcon** (`severityIcon.tsx`): Reusable severity icon component with SVG icons for success, info, warning, error - used by Alert, AlertDialog, AlertDrawer

**Screen Layout Components** (`src/screens/layout/`):
- **ScreenLayout** (`screenLayout.tsx`): Base screen layout with breadcrumbs, toolbar, and content area
  - Breadcrumbs navigation at top
  - Toolbar area with tools and hidden tools support
  - Content area with configurable padding
  - Integrated AlertDrawer for additional details
- **LocationBreadcrumbs** (`locationBreadcrumbs.tsx`): Breadcrumbs component for screen navigation
  - Takes array of `Breadcrumb` objects with route and label
  - Automatically disables last breadcrumb (current location)
  - Integrates with NavLink for navigation
- **CRUDScreen** (`crudScreen.tsx`): Full-featured CRUD operations screen
  - Intents: `none`, `view`, `edit`, `edit-record`, `action`
  - Built-in validation with validator integration
  - State management: dataNew, dataModified, dataLoading, dataSaving, dataCanceling
  - Standard CRUD operations: refresh, save, cancel, delete
  - Navigation prevention when data is modified (unsaved changes dialog)
  - Action buttons: save, cancel, delete, refresh (shown based on intent)
  - Event hooks: onRefresh, onModify, onValidate, onSave, onCancel, onDelete
- **TabsScreen** (`tabsScreen.tsx`): Tabbed interface wrapper for CRUDScreen
  - Combines TabsContainer with CRUDScreen functionality
  - All CRUD operations available within tab context
  - Validation across all tabs
  - Tab state managed by TabsContainer

**Toast Notification Patterns**:
- **Global Alerts**: Use AppAlertManager via message bus (`Alert.Success`, `Alert.Information`, `Alert.Warning`, `Alert.Error`) for app-wide notifications
- **Local Toasts**: Use AlertToast as child component for screen-specific notifications with custom lifecycle

**Routing Architecture** (`src/core/infrastructure/` and `src/components/navigation/`):

Multi-layout routing system with separation of concerns:

- **Router** (`src/components/navigation/router.tsx`): Generic routing engine (reusable component)
  - Takes `routes` object mapping paths to component functions
  - Supports dynamic path params: `/users/:id` → `route.params.id`
  - Supports query params: `?:tab` → `route.params.tab`
  - Uses regex-based route matching for flexibility
  - Manages route state and triggers view updates
  - Type: `Route<Routing>` provides type-safe route definitions

- **AppRouter** (`src/core/infrastructure/appRouter.tsx`): Application routing orchestrator
  - Manages two layout systems: `appLayout` and `otherLayout`
  - Routes between layouts based on path matching
  - Integrates with browsing history for navigation state
  - Message handlers:
    * `App.Router.GetRoute` - Get current route
    * `App.Router.GoToRoute` - Navigate with history tracking
    * `App.Router.SetRoute` - Navigate without history tracking
    * `App.Router.SetRouteParams` - Update route params
    * `App.Router.OpenNewTab` - Open route in new browser tab
    * `App.Router.BeforeRouteChange` - Hook before navigation
    * `App.Router.AfterRouteChange` - Hook after navigation

- **AppLayout** (`src/core/layout/appLayout.tsx`): Main application layout
  - Uses Router with `screenRoutes` from appRoutes.tsx
  - Includes AppSideBar with navigation menu
  - For authenticated application screens
  - Wraps content in Row with dividers and spacing (sideBar + router)

- **AppSideBar** (`src/core/layout/appSideBar.tsx`): Collapsible navigation sidebar
  - Collapsible state: collapsed (60px) or expanded (200px)
  - Toggle button with hamburger SVG icon (menu when collapsed, menu-open when expanded)
  - Contains AppMenu component with iconsOnly binding to collapsed state
  - Title "UECA Tutorial" shown when expanded
  - Plain HTML div with CSS transitions, no Material-UI

- **AppMenu** (`src/core/layout/appMenu.tsx`): Navigation menu with menu items
  - Contains NavItem children (homeMenuItem with SVG home icon)
  - iconsOnly prop hides text labels when sidebar collapsed
  - Route synchronization: _syncActiveMenu() marks active item based on current route
  - Uses plain HTML div instead of Material-UI List
  - All icons are SVG (no Material-UI icons)

- **OtherLayout** (`src/core/layout/otherLayout.tsx`): Minimal standalone layout
  - Uses Router with `otherRoutes` from appRoutes.tsx
  - No decorations or navigation chrome
  - For external redirects, document viewers, print views
  - Directly renders route view without wrapper

- **Route Definitions** (`src/core/infrastructure/appRoutes.tsx`):
  - `screenRoutes`: Main app routes (e.g., `/`, `/home`, `/users/:id`)
  - `otherRoutes`: Standalone routes for external URLs (e.g., `https://ueca-react.carrd.co/`, `https://github.com/nekutuzov/ueca-react-app`) and document viewers (e.g., `//printview`)
  - Type exports: `ScreenRoute`, `OtherRoute`, `AppRoute`, `AppRouteParams<T>`

**Color Palette System** (`src/core/infrastructure/appTheme.ts`):
- Centralized color definitions in `paletteColors` object
- `Palette` type for type-safe color references
- `resolvePaletteColor()` helper converts palette tokens to CSS colors
- All components should use `Palette` type for color props
- Supports both palette tokens (`"primary.main"`) and direct CSS colors (`"#1976d2"`)

**Infrastructure Components**:
- **ErrorFallback** (`src/components/utility/errorFallback.tsx`): React error boundary for graceful error handling
- **Spinner** (`src/components/misc/spinner.tsx`): Loading indicator with SVG animations (indeterminate/determinate)
- **AppBusyDisplay** (`src/core/infrastructure/appBusyDisplay.tsx`): Global busy state manager with delayed spinner
- **AppDialogManager** (`src/core/infrastructure/appDialogManager.tsx`): Centralized dialog management via message bus
- **AppAlertManager** (`src/core/infrastructure/appAlertManager.tsx`): Global toast notification system via message bus
  - Uses AlertToast components for each alert with position-based tracking
  - Supports 6 positioning options via `anchorOrigin` prop: top/bottom × left/center/right
  - Default position: `{ vertical: "bottom", horizontal: "right" }`
  - Auto-dismisses alerts after 4 seconds
- **FileSelector** (`src/components/misc/fileSelector.tsx`): Hidden file input for programmatic file selection
- **AppSecurity** (`src/core/infrastructure/appSecurity.tsx`): Authentication and authorization management
  - Stores UserContext (user, apiToken) in internal state
  - Provides `isAuthorized()`, `authorize()`, `unauthorize()` methods
  - Message handlers: `App.Security.IsAuthorized`, `App.Security.AuthorizeNative`, `App.Security.Unauthorize`
- **AppLoginForm** (`src/core/infrastructure/appLoginForm.tsx`): Login form component
  - Email/password inputs with TextField components
  - Remember me checkbox
  - Calls `App.Security.AuthorizeNative` message on submit
  - Plain HTML/CSS card layout (no Material-UI)
- **AppRouter** (`src/core/infrastructure/appRouter.tsx`): Routing orchestrator managing AppLayout and OtherLayout
- **AppLayout** (`src/core/layout/appLayout.tsx`): Main app layout with navigation chrome
- **OtherLayout** (`src/core/layout/otherLayout.tsx`): Minimal layout for standalone pages
- **AppUI** (`src/core/infrastructure/appUI.tsx`): UI orchestration layer integrating all infrastructure components
  - Conditionally renders AppLoginForm (unauthorized) or AppRouter (authorized)
  - Receives `authorizedMode` prop from Application via binding to `security.isAuthorized()`

## Development Workflows

**Development Server**: `npm run dev` (Vite on port 5001, base path `/myapp`)
**Production Build**: `npm run build` (TypeScript compilation + Vite build)
**Linting**: `npm run lint` (ESLint with TypeScript support)

**API Mocking**: MSW (Mock Service Worker) configured in `src/api/mocks/handlers.ts`:
- Enable/disable: Comment/uncomment `initMocks()` in `src/main.tsx`
- Service worker: `public/mockServiceWorker.js` (served at `/myapp/mockServiceWorker.js`)

**Component Creation Pattern** (follow exactly):
1. Create a folder for the component in the appropriate category (buttons/, inputs/, popups/, flyouts/, navigation/, tabs/, etc.)
2. Define `XxxStruct` type extending appropriate base
3. Create `XxxParams` and `XxxModel` type aliases
4. Create `useXxx` hook with structured implementation
5. Export `Xxx` component using `getFC(useXxx)`
6. Always export `XxxModel`, `XxxParams`, `useXxx`, and `Xxx`
7. Always set `id: useXxx.name` in props
8. Use `model.htmlId()` for root element `id` attribute
9. **One Folder Per Component** - component files (tsx + css) in dedicated folder
10. Create accompanying CSS file in same folder for component styles

**Specialized Component Factories Pattern**:
Create pre-configured variants of components by wrapping hooks with preset properties:
```tsx
// Base component
function useIconButton(params?: IconButtonParams): IconButtonModel { /* ... */ }

// Specialized factory (removes iconView from params, presets the icon)
type CloseIconButtonParams = Omit<IconButtonParams, "iconView">;

function useCloseIconButton(params?: CloseIconButtonParams): IconButtonModel {
    return useIconButton({
        ...params,
        iconView: <svg>...</svg>  // Preset icon
    });
}

const CloseIconButton = UECA.getFC(useCloseIconButton);
```
**When to use**: For common configuration variants (icon buttons, form buttons, alerts). Not for behavioral changes.
**See**: `Specialized Component Factories in UECA-React.md` documentation in project root

**Component Structure Example**:
```tsx
import * as UECA from "ueca-react";
import { UIBaseModel, UIBaseParams, UIBaseStruct, useUIBase } from "@components";

type MyComponentStruct = UIBaseStruct<{
    props: {
        value: string;
    };
    events: {
        onChange: (value: string) => void;
    };
}>;

type MyComponentParams = UIBaseParams<MyComponentStruct>;
type MyComponentModel = UIBaseModel<MyComponentStruct>;

function useMyComponent(params?: MyComponentParams): MyComponentModel {
    const struct: MyComponentStruct = {
        props: {
            id: useMyComponent.name,
            value: "",
        },
        
        View: () => <div id={model.htmlId()}>{model.value}</div>
    };
    
    const model = useUIBase(struct, params);
    return model;
}

const MyComponent = UECA.getFC(useMyComponent);

export { MyComponentModel, MyComponentParams, useMyComponent, MyComponent };
```

## Critical Conventions

**No React.StrictMode**: Explicitly avoided due to UECA lifecycle conflicts

**Lifecycle Hooks**: Use UECA hooks instead of useEffect:
- `constr(model)` - one-time setup when model instantiated
- `init(model)` - called on creation or cache retrieval
- `mount(model)` - when component attaches to DOM
- `draw(model)` - after view rendering
- `erase(model)` - before UI removal
- `unmount(model)` - when component detaches from DOM
- `deinit(model)` - when component loses React context

**State Management**: Direct property assignment (MobX-powered):
```tsx
model.count++; // triggers reactive updates
model.user = newUser; // no setState needed
```

**Property Bindings**: Three types for parent-child data flow:
```tsx
// 1. Unidirectional (read-only)
disabled: () => model.isLoading

// 2. Bidirectional (two-way sync)
value: UECA.bind(() => model.formData, "username")

// 3. Custom (with transformation)
phone: UECA.bind(
    () => formatPhone(model.phoneDigits),
    (val) => model.phoneDigits = stripFormat(val)
)
```

**Type Casting for Bindings**: When component expects broader type than model property provides:
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Cast the entire binding result
value={UECA.bind(() => model, "variant") as UECA.Bond<string | number>}
checked={UECA.bind(() => model, "disabled")}  // No cast needed for matching types

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use custom binding with manual setters for simple type mismatches
value={UECA.bind(() => model.variant as string | number, (v) => model.variant = v as "text" | "outlined")}

// Use case: RadioGroup/Select expect string | number, but model has union literals or Palette type
// Solution: Cast binding to UECA.Bond<string | number> - maintains bidirectional sync automatically
```

**Critical for Focus Management**: Always use `UECA.bind()` for input components to maintain stable references across re-renders. Without bindings, onChange handlers are recreated on every render, causing inputs to lose focus while typing.

**Centralized Error Handling**: All errors caught by `UECA.globalSettings.errorHandler`:
```tsx
UECA.globalSettings.errorHandler = (error: Error) => {
    appMessageBus.unicast("App.UnhandledException", error);
};
```

**Automatic Event Handlers**: UECA generates events for all props:
```tsx
// onChange<Prop> - fires AFTER property updates
events: {
    onChangeValue: (newVal, oldVal) => { 
        console.log("Value changed"); 
    }
}

// onChanging<Prop> - fires BEFORE update (can transform or block)
events: {
    onChangingValue: (newVal, oldVal) => {
        if (newVal < 0) return oldVal;  // Block invalid changes
        return newVal.toUpperCase();  // Transform before setting
    }
}
```

## Best Practices

**Component Encapsulation**:
- Prefer passing domain objects over many individual properties
- Handle data transformations internally, not in consuming components
- Keep interfaces minimal and cohesive

**JSX Structure**:
- Keep JSX clean and structural
- Move algorithmic logic to private functions (prefix with `_`)
- Break large JSX into private observer View methods for precise re-rendering

**Observer View Methods**:
For complex screens with multiple independent sections, define private View methods as model methods:
```tsx
methods: {
    _PropertiesEditorView: () => React.ReactElement;
    _PreviewAreaView: () => React.ReactElement;
}

// Implementation in methods section
methods: {
    _PropertiesEditorView: () => {
        return (
            <Col spacing="medium">
                <TextField value={UECA.bind(() => model, "inputValue")} />
                {/* More inputs */}
            </Col>
        );
    }
}

// Use in contentView
contentView: () => (
    <Row>
        {model._PropertiesEditorView()}
        {model._PreviewAreaView()}
    </Row>
)
```
Benefits:
- Methods become MobX observers - only re-render when their dependencies change
- Prevents entire component tree recreation on property changes
- Maintains component identity - critical for input focus management
- Improves performance by isolating re-render boundaries

**Component Integration**:
- **Direct Model Calls**: Parent → Child only
- **Message Bus**: Any → Any for decoupled communication
- **Never** call parent from child directly

**Component Wrapping Pattern**:
When one component wraps another to extend functionality, use bidirectional bindings for one-to-one property mapping:
```tsx
// NavItem wraps NavLink to add visual presentation
props: {
    route: UECA.bind(() => model.navLink, "route"),
    disabled: UECA.bind(() => model.navLink, "disabled"),
    newTab: UECA.bind(() => model.navLink, "newTab"),
    text: UECA.bind(() => model.navLink, "title"),  // Maps to NavLink's 'title'
}
```
Benefits:
- Transparent API - users don't need to know about internal children
- Automatic synchronization - changes flow bidirectionally
- Single source of truth - child owns logic, parent adds presentation
- Clean separation of concerns

**CSS Best Practices**:
- **CSS should only handle appearance**: colors, backgrounds, borders, border-radius, transitions
- **Layout & behavior in JSX**: Use Block/Row/Col props for padding, cursor, alignment, spacing, sizing
- **Use CSS variables for theme colors**: Define colors in appTheme.ts, apply via CSS variables with `resolvePaletteColor()`
- **Keep CSS files minimal**: Avoid layout properties (display, width, padding, align-items, etc.) in CSS
```tsx
// Good: Layout in JSX, appearance in CSS
<Block
    className="nav-item"
    padding="small"
    cursor="pointer"
    sx={{
        "--nav-item-hover": resolvePaletteColor("menu.hover")
    } as React.CSSProperties}
>
    {content}
</Block>

// CSS: .nav-item { background-color: transparent; transition: background-color 0.2s; }
// CSS: .nav-item:hover { background-color: var(--nav-item-hover); }
```

**Using Layout Components**:
```tsx
// Row for horizontal layouts
<Row horizontalAlign="spaceBetween" spacing="small" fill>
    <Block>Left</Block>
    <Block>Right</Block>
</Row>

// Col for vertical layouts
<Col verticalAlign="center" fill backgroundColor="background.paper">
    <Block>Header</Block>
    <Block fill>Content</Block>
</Col>
```

**Using Color Palette**:
```tsx
// Import from core
import { Palette, resolvePaletteColor } from "@core";

// Use palette tokens
<Block backgroundColor="primary.main">...</Block>
<Spinner color="info.light" />

// Or direct CSS colors as fallback
<Block backgroundColor="#ff5722">...</Block>
```

**Showing Busy State**:
```tsx
// Show spinner
